The paper proposes a clustering technique for analyzing smart meter data, which involves feature selection and self-organizing maps. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with managing power demand and increasing energy consumption efficiency, which falls under the umbrella of Sustainability (cs.SI) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of a genetic algorithm also suggests that the paper may belong to the Data Mining (cs.DM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with managing power demand, which is a control problem, suggesting that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
